## Project Architecture

- **Product**: Discursive — host Go CLI/daemon (macOS/Linux)
- **Purpose**: Local OpenAI-compatible gateway that sanitizes Cursor payloads,
  routes by **alias→provider→model** to **Moonshot Kimi** and/or **DeepSeek**,
  exposes a public HTTPS tunnel (Cursor cloud cannot hit localhost). Cursor is
  configured manually with the gateway API key (never upstream provider keys)
- **Providers**: Moonshot (`kimi-k3`, `kimi-k2.6`) and
 DeepSeek (`deepseek-v4-flash`, `deepseek-v4-pro`) and
 Thaura (`thaura`). Switching is **setting the
 Cursor alias** — see alias map in `gateway.mdc` / `cursor-settings.mdc`
- **Runtime**: Go **1.26.5+**; host process — **not** Docker-primary, **not** Wails/Vue/Tauri
- **CLI**: [Cobra](https://cobra.dev/) (`internal/cli/`); **no Viper** — config in `internal/config`
- **Reference**: `examples/use-kimi-on-cursor/` (study/port; do not vendor Rust/TS);
  OpenAI shapes: `examples/openai-openapi/`
- **Docs**: https://platform.kimi.ai/ · https://api-docs.deepseek.com/

```
main.go             # Cobra CLI entry (start/stop/status/doctor/usage/…)
internal/cli/       # Cobra command tree (`root.go`, `start.go`, …)
internal/
  config/            # settings, paths, portable mode
  crypto/            # secrets + gateway key generation
  gateway/           # HTTP server, auth, sanitizer, responses adapter, optimizer
  tunnel/            # cloudflared Quick Tunnel (+ BYO URL mode)
  usage/             # pricing table + per-session accounting
  doctor/            # health checks
examples/use-kimi-on-cursor/  # behavioral reference
.cursor/rules/       # this tree
.claude/skills/      # invocable agent skills
```

### Inspiration sources (hard)

- Study `examples/use-kimi-on-cursor/` (sanitizer, adapter, tunnel, Cursor patch).
  **Reimplement in Go.** Never vendor, transpile, or paste that tree into the
  product binary tree.
- OpenAI request/response shapes: consult `examples/openai-openapi/` when present
  (reference only; do not ship in the binary).
- Kimi/Moonshot details: `.cursor/rules/kimi.mdc`. If incomplete, fetch
  https://platform.kimi.ai/docs/ (start at llms.txt).
- DeepSeek details: `.cursor/rules/deepseek.mdc`. If incomplete, fetch
 https://api-docs.deepseek.com/.
- Thaura AI details: `.cursor/rules/thaura.mdc`. If incomplete, fetch
 https://thaura.ai/api-platform.
- Never name Claude Code (or inspiration origin) in product source, comments,
  user-facing copy, or commit messages for product code. Planning/rules may say
  at most “inspired by Claude Code.”

