## Safety / Workflow Rails

### No-Go Operations

NEVER do these without explicit user approval:
- Modify `.cursor/rules/` files (except via `/dialectic-of-cognition` skill)
- Commit or push to git **outside** `/task-3-complete` (that skill commits and
  **pushes by default**; use `/task-3-complete TXX --no-push` to skip push)
- Force-push, rewrite shared history, or push secrets
- Put Moonshot/Kimi or DeepSeek API keys in Cursor settings, logs, diagnostics zips, or git
- Point Cursor Override Base URL at `127.0.0.1` / private IPs as a “fix”
- Make Docker the default runtime
- Run `docker`, `npm`, or `pnpm` unless the user explicitly requests

### `Pre-commit hook formatting not staged`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Pre-commit hook runs `make verify` (or `go fmt`) but formatting changes appear as unstaged modifications after the commit, leaving the working tree dirty | Lefthook (and git hooks in general) do not automatically re-stage files modified by hook commands — the commit captures the pre-format version and the formatted version is left unstaged | Append `&& git add $(git diff --name-only --diff-filter=M)` to the hook command so any file modified by the formatter is re-staged before the commit completes |

<!-- last-verified: 2026-07 -->

### Package Managers

- Go modules for the product
- Never use npm/pnpm/Yarn for the product (reference example under `examples/`
  may use them; do not copy that into the product tree)

### Verification Defaults

- Prefer **`make verify`** (lint + `go test ./...` + `go build ./...`) after
  substantive Go edits once Makefile exists
- Prefer **latest stable** releases for Go toolchain upgrades and new module
  deps when the environment allows (document pins if policy blocks upgrades)
- `/task-3-complete` **pushes** the completed branch by default (`--no-push` to
  skip) and must emit **Manual test** commands (or `Nothing to test` + why)
- Quick checks: `go build ./...` / `go vet ./...` / package tests under
  `internal/gateway`, `internal/usage`, `internal/tunnel`, `internal/cli`
- Integration proof: CLI start + doctor; live Agent path through public URL
- If verification fails, fix that layer — do not advance to the next

